('Information Technology', 'Cybersecurity', 'What is encryption?', '["Deleting data","Converting data into a coded format to prevent unauthorized access","Compressing files","Backing up data"]', 1, 'Encryption transforms readable data into ciphertext using algorithms, ensuring only authorized parties can access it.', 'foundational', 5),
('Information Technology', 'Cybersecurity', 'What is a firewall?', '["A physical wall","A network security system that monitors and controls incoming and outgoing traffic","An antivirus","A backup system"]', 1, 'A firewall acts as a barrier between trusted and untrusted networks, filtering traffic based on security rules.', 'foundational', 6),
('Information Technology', 'Cybersecurity', 'What is multi-factor authentication (MFA)?', '["Using a strong password","A security method requiring two or more verification factors to access an account","A type of encryption","A firewall setting"]', 1, 'MFA adds security layers by requiring multiple verification methods: something you know, have, or are.', 'developing', 7),
('Information Technology', 'Cybersecurity', 'What is a zero-day vulnerability?', '["An old bug","A security flaw unknown to the vendor that attackers can exploit before a fix is available","A patched vulnerability","A minor bug"]', 1, 'Zero-day vulnerabilities are unknown to the software vendor, giving them zero days to fix before potential exploitation.', 'advanced', 8),

('Information Technology', 'Cloud Infrastructure', 'What is the difference between IaaS, PaaS, and SaaS?', '["They are the same","IaaS provides infrastructure, PaaS provides platform tools, SaaS provides complete applications","IaaS is cheapest","SaaS is most complex"]', 1, 'IaaS offers raw compute/storage, PaaS adds development tools/runtime, SaaS delivers complete applications to end users.', 'foundational', 9),
('Information Technology', 'Cloud Infrastructure', 'What is a virtual machine?', '["A physical server","A software emulation of a physical computer that runs its own operating system","A container","A cloud storage bucket"]', 1, 'A virtual machine emulates a complete computer system, allowing multiple OS instances on a single physical machine.', 'foundational', 9),
('Information Technology', 'Cloud Infrastructure', 'What is DevOps?', '["A programming language","A set of practices combining software development and IT operations for faster, more reliable delivery","A cloud provider","A database"]', 1, 'DevOps bridges development and operations through automation, CI/CD, and collaboration for faster software delivery.', 'developing', 11),
('Information Technology', 'Cloud Infrastructure', 'What is a CI/CD pipeline?', '["A data pipeline","Continuous Integration/Continuous Deployment—automated processes for building, testing, and deploying code","A network cable","A security scan"]', 1, 'CI/CD automates the process of integrating code changes, running tests, and deploying to production environments.', 'developing', 12),
('Information Technology', 'Cloud Infrastructure', 'What is infrastructure as code?', '["Writing code on servers","Managing and provisioning infrastructure through machine-readable configuration files instead of manual processes","A coding standard","A database schema"]', 1, 'Infrastructure as Code (IaC) uses declarative files to automate infrastructure provisioning, ensuring consistency and repeatability.', 'advanced', 12),

('Information Technology', 'Database Management', 'What is the difference between SQL and NoSQL databases?', '["They are the same","SQL uses structured tables with relationships; NoSQL uses flexible schemas like documents or key-value pairs","SQL is newer","NoSQL is always faster"]', 1, 'SQL databases are relational with fixed schemas; NoSQL databases offer flexible schemas for unstructured or semi-structured data.', 'foundational', 13),
('Information Technology', 'Database Management', 'What is ACID in database transactions?', '["A chemical property","Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, Durability—properties ensuring reliable database transactions","A programming concept","A security standard"]', 1, 'ACID properties ensure database transactions are processed reliably: all-or-nothing, consistent, isolated, and permanent.', 'developing', 14),
('Information Technology', 'Database Management', 'What is database replication?', '["Copying a database to a USB","Maintaining copies of a database across multiple servers for reliability and performance","Backing up once","Deleting duplicates"]', 1, 'Database replication copies data across multiple servers, improving availability, fault tolerance, and read performance.', 'developing', 15),
('Information Technology', 'Database Management', 'What is a stored procedure?', '["A saved file","A precompiled collection of SQL statements stored in the database that can be executed as a unit","A backup method","A query log"]', 1, 'Stored procedures are reusable SQL code blocks that encapsulate business logic in the database for efficiency and security.', 'advanced', 16),
('Information Technology', 'Database Management', 'What is data integrity?', '["Data speed","The accuracy, consistency, and reliability of data throughout its lifecycle","Data size","Data format"]', 1, 'Data integrity ensures data remains accurate, consistent, and trustworthy from creation through its entire lifecycle.', 'foundational', 13),

('Information Technology', 'Linux Administration', 'What is the Linux terminal?', '["A graphical interface","A command-line interface for interacting with the operating system","A web browser","A text editor"]', 1, 'The Linux terminal provides a text-based interface for executing commands, managing files, and administering the system.', 'foundational', 17),
('Information Technology', 'Linux Administration', 'What does the chmod command do?', '["Creates files","Changes file permissions to control read, write, and execute access","Deletes files","Moves files"]', 1, 'chmod modifies file permissions, controlling who can read, write, or execute files and directories.', 'foundational', 17),
('Information Technology', 'Linux Administration', 'What is a cron job?', '["A type of virus","A scheduled task that runs automatically at specified intervals","A log file","A network service"]', 1, 'Cron jobs schedule automated command execution at specified times and intervals using crontab configuration.', 'developing', 18),
('Information Technology', 'Linux Administration', 'What is SSH?', '["A programming language","Secure Shell—a protocol for securely accessing and managing remote servers","A file type","A database"]', 1, 'SSH provides encrypted communication for securely connecting to and administering remote servers.', 'foundational', 18),
('Information Technology', 'Linux Administration', 'What is a package manager in Linux?', '["A shipping service","A tool that automates installing, updating, and removing software packages","A file organizer","A system monitor"]', 1, 'Package managers (apt, yum, dnf) handle software installation, updates, and dependency management automatically.', 'developing', 19),

('Information Technology', 'ITIL & Service Management', 'What is ITIL?', '["A programming language","A framework of best practices for IT service management","A database","A security standard"]', 1, 'ITIL (Information Technology Infrastructure Library) provides structured best practices for delivering IT services.', 'foundational', 21),
('Information Technology', 'ITIL & Service Management', 'What is an SLA?', '["A software license","A Service Level Agreement defining the expected level of service between provider and customer","A security log","A type of API"]', 1, 'An SLA is a formal agreement defining service expectations, metrics, and responsibilities between parties.', 'foundational', 21),
('Information Technology', 'ITIL & Service Management', 'What is incident management?', '["Preventing all errors","The process of restoring normal service operation as quickly as possible after an unplanned interruption","Creating incidents","Logging changes"]', 1, 'Incident management aims to restore normal service operations quickly while minimizing business impact.', 'developing', 22),
('Information Technology', 'ITIL & Service Management', 'What is change management in IT?', '["Changing passwords","A systematic approach to handling changes in IT infrastructure to minimize disruption","Upgrading hardware","Hiring new staff"]', 1, 'Change management ensures changes are implemented smoothly through planning, testing, and approval processes.', 'developing', 23),
('Information Technology', 'ITIL & Service Management', 'What is the difference between a problem and an incident in ITIL?', '["They are the same","An incident is an unplanned interruption; a problem is the underlying root cause of incidents","Problems are worse","Incidents are planned"]', 1, 'Incidents are symptoms requiring immediate resolution; problems are root causes requiring investigation and permanent fixes.', 'advanced', 24);
